hubBasicID.name: hubBasicID
hubBasicID.description: A 48-bit unique identifier, the hub ethernet address is used.

hubCardCapacity.name: hubCardCapacity
hubCardCapacity.description: The number of groups (cards) that can be contained within the hub.

hubCardMap.name: hubCardMap
hubCardMap.description: A string of bits which reflects the current configuration of units which are viewed by the Group managed objects. The length of the bitstring is hubGroupCapacity bits. The LSBit relates to the unit viewed by group 1. A '1' in the bitstring indicates presence of the unit, '0' represent absence of the unit.

hubNumOfRelays.name: hubNumOfRelays
hubNumOfRelays.description: Shows the number of relays present without regard as to whether or not each is enabled or disabled.

hubRelayActive.name: hubRelayActive
hubRelayActive.description: An integer that indicates which relay is active. Zero indicates that no relays are active.

hubResourceType.name: hubResourceType
hubResourceType.description: An integer value representing the IEEE802 Standard that applies to this resource.

hubStandardRevision.name: hubStandardRevision
hubStandardRevision.description: An integer value representing the revision of the IEEE802 Standard to which the station conforms with respect to that resource.

hubIEEE8023LmeOptions.name: hubIEEE8023LmeOptions
hubIEEE8023LmeOptions.description: A set of option indicators, each of which, if present, indicates that a particular option within NM_LME is supported. Its interpretation is specified in the appropriate standard.

hubManID.name: hubManID
hubManID.description: A 24 bit value that identifies the manufacturer.

hubManTelephoneNum.name: hubManTelephoneNum
hubManTelephoneNum.description: An ascii representation of the manufacturer's telephone number.

hubName.name: hubName
hubName.description: This attribute is a text string up to 32 characters, of locally determined significance.

hubIPaddress.name: hubIPaddress
hubIPaddress.description: This attribute contains the IP address of the hub.

hubEEpromRev.name: hubEEpromRev
hubEEpromRev.description: This attribute provides the eeprom revision number and is read from the hardware.

hubSecureMode.name: hubSecureMode
hubSecureMode.description: An integer value to set the hub in secure mode. In secure mode all ports are disabled by default, otherwise ports are enabled by default upon creation.

hmBasicCardTable.name: hmBasicCardTable
hmBasicCardTable.description: This table provide a management view of the HUB configuration specific to individual cards.

gCardID.name: gCardID
gCardID.description: An 8 bit value unique within the hub.

gCardNumberOfPorts.name: gCardNumberOfPorts
gCardNumberOfPorts.description: This attribute contains the number of ports in the card object instance (MAC Entities).

gCardName.name: gCardName
gCardName.description: This attribute is a text string up to 32 characters, of locally determined significance.

gCardType.name: gCardType
gCardType.description: This attribute contains the type of card.

gCardRingNumberA.name: gCardRingNumberA
gCardRingNumberA.description: This attribute contains the Ring number associated with a UTP2112 type of card, or with RI/RO set of ports 'A' for a STP4104 type of card.

gCardRingNumberB.name: gCardRingNumberB
gCardRingNumberB.description: This attribute contains the Ring number associated with RI/RO set of ports 'B' for a STP4104 type of card.

gCardIbmModeA.name: gCardIbmModeA
gCardIbmModeA.description: This attribute specifies wether RI/RO set of ports 'A' for a STP4104 type of card is in IBM mode or normal mode.

gCardIbmModeB.name: gCardIbmModeB
gCardIbmModeB.description: This attribute specifies wether RI/RO set of ports 'B' for a STP4104 type of card is in IBM mode or normal mode.

gCardRingSpeedA.name: gCardRingSpeedA
gCardRingSpeedA.description: This attribute specifies wether RI/RO set of ports 'A' for a STP4104 runs at 4 or 16 Mbps. It is also used to display the speed of a UTP2112 type of cards.

gCardRingSpeedB.name: gCardRingSpeedB
gCardRingSpeedB.description: This attribute specifies wether RI/RO set of ports 'B' for a STP4104 runs at 4 or 16 Mbps.

hmBasicPortTable.name: hmBasicPortTable
hmBasicPortTable.description: This table provide a management view of the HUB configuration specific to individual ports.

gCardBasicID.name: gCardBasicID
gCardBasicID.description: An 8 bit value unique within the hub.

gPortID.name: gPortID
gPortID.description: An 8 bit value unique in the group.

gPortAdminState.name: gPortAdminState
gPortAdminState.description: Indicates whether the port is enabled or disabled. A disabled port neither transmit nor receives.

gPortAutoPartitionState.name: gPortAutoPartitionState
gPortAutoPartitionState.description: Indicates whether the port is currently partitioned by the hub's auto-partition protection.

gPortName.name: gPortName
gPortName.description: This attribute is a text string up to 32 characters, of locally determined significance.

hubSelfTestID.name: hubSelfTestID
hubSelfTestID.description: A 48-bit unique identifier, the hub ethernet address is used.

hubTimeSinceReset.name: hubTimeSinceReset
hubTimeSinceReset.description: The time in tens of milliseconds since the last time that the system was reset. This counter has a value of 0 when initialized.

hubResetTimeStamp.name: hubResetTimeStamp
hubResetTimeStamp.description: Not a counter, this attribute provides the value of hubTimeSinceReset when the hub was last reset.

hubHealthState.name: hubHealthState
hubHealthState.description: This attribute will store the results of the startup diagnostics. The first octet indicates the overall results of the startup tests, while the remaining 8 octets will contain the results of the individual test. Each octet will contain a 1 if the test was passed, 2 if the test failed. The following list defines the meanings of each octet in the string: Octet 1 - overall test result Octet 2 - system NMI test Octet 3 - system timers test Octet 4 - system DMA test Octet 5 - 82586 test Octet 6 - backplane ethernet address test Octet 7 - NVRAM test Octet 8 - dual port RAM test Octet 9 - real time clock test

hubHealthText.name: hubHealthText
hubHealthText.description: This attribute provides a textual description of which test, if any, failed during diagnostics.

hubHealthData.name: hubHealthData
hubHealthData.description: This attribute provides a textual description of which test, if any, failed during diagnostics.

hubSystemResetting.name: hubSystemResetting
hubSystemResetting.description: Indicates whether the hub is in the process of resetting completely (coldstart).

hubResetting.name: hubResetting
hubResetting.description: Indicates whether the hub is in the process of resetting or not (warmstart).

hubExecutingSelfTest.name: hubExecutingSelfTest
hubExecutingSelfTest.description: Indicates whether the hub is in the process of executing self diagnostics.

hubResetAction.name: hubResetAction
hubResetAction.description: Restart the hub if selecting reset.

hmPerfMonRelayTable.name: hmPerfMonRelayTable
hmPerfMonRelayTable.description: This table provide a management view individual relay performance capability.

relayPerfID.name: relayPerfID
relayPerfID.description: This attribute is the value used in addressing the relay.

relayTotalCollisions.name: relayTotalCollisions
relayTotalCollisions.description: The counter is incremented every time the hub enters a condition caused by simultaneous transmission and detection of external activity on one or more of its ports.

hmPerfMonPortTable.name: hmPerfMonPortTable
hmPerfMonPortTable.description: This table provide a management view of individual ports performance capability.

gCardPerfID.name: gCardPerfID
gCardPerfID.description: This attribute represent the card number and is used to address the performance monitoring table.

gPortPerfID.name: gPortPerfID
gPortPerfID.description: This attribute represent the port number and is used to address the performance monitoring table.

gPortReadableFrames.name: gPortReadableFrames
gPortReadableFrames.description: A representation of the total frames of legal length that have not been corrupted in transmission counted by the port object.

gPortReadableOctets.name: gPortReadableOctets
gPortReadableOctets.description: It is sum of data and padding octets contained in ReadableFrames counted by the port object.

gPortPygmys.name: gPortPygmys
gPortPygmys.description: The sum of pygmy frame fragments counted by the port object. They occur when a frame fragment was received which was not in collision and was not recognized as a valid ethernet packet. They normally make up less than 5% of Rx frames on hub-to-hub or hub-to-backbone connections and < 1% of total Rx frames for hub-DTE connections. Significantly higher levels may indicate external noise hits on the cabling, i.e. UTP in a noisy environment.

gPortRunts.name: gPortRunts
gPortRunts.description: The sum of frames which were received then collided with another fram(e)s received by the hub. The port(s) which receive the collider frame(s) will increment their gPortCollisions and the port which was collided with will increment this counter. It is possible to count more runts than collisions for a specific port. As a rough guideline, less than 5% of the Rx frames should be runts.

gPortFrameCheckSeqErrs.name: gPortFrameCheckSeqErrs
gPortFrameCheckSeqErrs.description: The sum of frames received on this port that are an integral number of octets in length and do not pass the FCS check. Normally less than 1% of Rx frames. Could be caused by line noise, loose connections, a faulty DTE, or a faulty hub.

gPortAlignmentErrors.name: gPortAlignmentErrors
gPortAlignmentErrors.description: The sum of frames received on this port that are not an integral number of octets in length. Should be less than 1% of the total number of Rx frames and greater than or equal to gPortFramesTooLong and gPortFrameCheckSeqErrors. Could be caused by line noise, loose connections, a faulty DTE, or a faulty hub.

gPortFramesTooLong.name: gPortFramesTooLong
gPortFramesTooLong.description: The sum of frames received on this port that are more than 1518 octets long. Should be < 1% of the total number of Rx frames. Could be caused by a faulty DTE or a faulty hub.

gPortAutoPartitionCount.name: gPortAutoPartitionCount
gPortAutoPartitionCount.description: It is the number of times that this port has been automatically partitioned.

gPortLateCollisions.name: gPortLateCollisions
gPortLateCollisions.description: This attribute is the total number of late collisions experienced by the port object. Usually indicates a DTE trying to Tx w/o checking the Ethernet for traffic first. May be due to a hardware fault on the sending DTE, or a segment which is too long for collision detection to work properly. Should normally be < 1% of total Rx frames.

gPortCollisions.name: gPortCollisions
gPortCollisions.description: This attribute provides the total number of collisions encountered by the port object. The port that was collided with will count a runt. Normally less than 5% of the Rx frames should be collisions. Numbers significantly higher than this may indicate hardware problems or congestion.

gPortAlarms.name: gPortAlarms
gPortAlarms.description: The number of times a threshold was exceeded on that port.

gPortMulticastFrames.name: gPortMulticastFrames
gPortMulticastFrames.description: This attribute contains a count of frames successfully received by the port and are directed to an active non-broadcast group of addresses.

gPortBroadcastFrames.name: gPortBroadcastFrames
gPortBroadcastFrames.description: This attribute contains the total number of broadcast frames received by the port object since system restart.

hmAddrTrackPortTable.name: hmAddrTrackPortTable
hmAddrTrackPortTable.description: This table provide a management view of individual port address tracking capability.

gCardAddrID.name: gCardAddrID
gCardAddrID.description: An 8 bit value unique within the hub.

gPortAddrID.name: gPortAddrID
gPortAddrID.description: An 8 bit value unique within the group.

gPortLastSourceAddress.name: gPortLastSourceAddress
gPortLastSourceAddress.description: The source (ethernet) address of the last ReadableFrame received by this port.

gPortSourceAddrChanges.name: gPortSourceAddrChanges
gPortSourceAddrChanges.description: This attribute counts the number of times the last source address has changed.

bridgeBaseAddress.name: bridgeBaseAddress
bridgeBaseAddress.description: The MAC address used by this bridge when it must be referred to in a unique fashion. It is recommended that this be the numerically smallest MAC address of all ports that belong to this bridge. However it is only required to be unique.

bridgeNumPorts.name: bridgeNumPorts
bridgeNumPorts.description: The number of (logical) ports controlled by this bridging entity.

bridgeType.name: bridgeType
bridgeType.description: Indicates what type of bridging this bridge can perform. If a bridge is actually performing a certain type of bridging this will be indicated by entries in the port table for the given type.

bridgeNumOfInterfaces.name: bridgeNumOfInterfaces
bridgeNumOfInterfaces.description: The number of interfaces controlled by this bridging entity, the interface stats are managed by MIB II interface group.

bridgePowerUpStatus.name: bridgePowerUpStatus
bridgePowerUpStatus.description: This attribute contains the result of any non fatal hardware diagnostics performed during the power on procedure.

bridgeIpAddr.name: bridgeIpAddr
bridgeIpAddr.description: This attribute contains the IP address of the bridge.

bridgeManID.name: bridgeManID
bridgeManID.description: This is a 24 bit value that identifies the manufacturer.

bridgeManProductVersion.name: bridgeManProductVersion
bridgeManProductVersion.description: This attribute provides the software revision number.

bridgeEEpromRev.name: bridgeEEpromRev
bridgeEEpromRev.description: This attribute provides the eeprom revision number and is read from the hardware.

bridgeSerialNum.name: bridgeSerialNum
bridgeSerialNum.description: This attribute provides the EBM Serial Number and is read from the hardware.

bridgeHubChassis.name: bridgeHubChassis
bridgeHubChassis.description: This attribute provides information on the type of Hub Chassis this bridge is currently using.

filterDatabaseSize.name: filterDatabaseSize
filterDatabaseSize.description: This attribute represents the number of entries into the filtering database.

numberOfDynamicEntries.name: numberOfDynamicEntries
numberOfDynamicEntries.description: This attribute contains a number of dynamic entries currently in the Filtering Database.

numberOfStaticEntries.name: numberOfStaticEntries
numberOfStaticEntries.description: This attribute contains a number of static entries currently in the Filtering Database.

agingState.name: agingState
agingState.description: When this attribute is ON, the Bridge will age dynamic station entries from the filter table automatically.

agingTime.name: agingTime
agingTime.description: The timeout period in seconds for aging out dynamically learned forwarding information.

learningState.name: learningState
learningState.description: When this attribute is ON, the Bridge will learn LAN station addresses automatically.

protocolFilterState.name: protocolFilterState
protocolFilterState.description: This attribute specifies whether protocol filtering is enabled or disabled.

broadcastForwardingState.name: broadcastForwardingState
broadcastForwardingState.description: This attribute specifies whether broadcast frames are being forwarded.

multicastForwardingState.name: multicastForwardingState
multicastForwardingState.description: This attribute specifies whether multicast frames are being forwarded.

bridgeTpFdbTable.name: bridgeTpFdbTable
bridgeTpFdbTable.description: A table that contains information about unicast entries for which the bridge has forwarding and/or filtering information. This information is used by the transparent bridging function in determining how to propagate a received frame.

bridgeTpFdbEntry.name: bridgeTpFdbEntry
bridgeTpFdbEntry.description: Information about a specific unicast MAC address for which the bridge has some forwarding and/or filtering information.

bridgeDot1dTpFdbAddress.name: bridgeDot1dTpFdbAddress
bridgeDot1dTpFdbAddress.description: A unicast MAC address for which the bridge has forwarding and/or filtering information.

bridgeDot1dTpFdbPort.name: bridgeDot1dTpFdbPort
bridgeDot1dTpFdbPort.description: Either the value '0', or the port number of the port on which a frame having a source address equal to the value of the corresponding instance of dot1dTpFdbAddress has been seen. A value of '0' indicates that the port number has not been learned but that the bridge does have some forwarding/filtering information about this address (e.g. in the dot1dStaticTable). Implementors are encouraged to assign the port value to this object whenever it is learned even for addresses for which the corresponding value of dot1dTpFdbStatus is not learned(3).

bridgeDot1dTpFdbStatus.name: bridgeDot1dTpFdbStatus
bridgeDot1dTpFdbStatus.description: The status of this entry. The meanings of the values are: other(1) : none of the following. This would include the case where some other MIB object (not the corresponding instance of dot1dTpFdbPort, nor an entry in the dot1dStaticTable) is being used to determine if and how frames addressed to the value of the corresponding instance of dot1dTpFdbAddress are being forwarded. invalid(2) : this entry is not longer valid (e.g., it was learned but has since aged-out), but has not yet been flushed from the table. learned(3) : the value of the corresponding instance of dot1dTpFdbPort was learned, and is being used. self(4) : the value of the corresponding instance of dot1dTpFdbAddress represents one of the bridge's addresses. The corresponding instance of dot1dTpFdbPort indicates which of the bridge's ports has this address. mgmt(5) : the value of the corresponding instance of dot1dTpFdbAddress is also the value of an existing instance of dot1dStaticAddress.

bridgeLogicalPortTable.name: bridgeLogicalPortTable
bridgeLogicalPortTable.description: A table that contains information about every port that is associated with this transparent bridge.

bridgeLogicalPortEntry.name: bridgeLogicalPortEntry
bridgeLogicalPortEntry.description: A list of information for each port of a transparent bridge.

bridgeDot1dTpPort.name: bridgeDot1dTpPort
bridgeDot1dTpPort.description: The port number of the port for which this entry contains Transparent bridging management information.

bridgeDot1dTpPortMaxInfo.name: bridgeDot1dTpPortMaxInfo
bridgeDot1dTpPortMaxInfo.description: The maximum size of the INFO (non-MAC) field that this port will receive or transmit.

bridgeDot1dTpPortInFrames.name: bridgeDot1dTpPortInFrames
bridgeDot1dTpPortInFrames.description: The number of frames that have been received by this port from its segment. Note that a frame received on the interface corresponding to this port is only counted by this object if and only if it is for a protocol being processed by the local bridging function.

bridgeDot1dTpPortOutFrames.name: bridgeDot1dTpPortOutFrames
bridgeDot1dTpPortOutFrames.description: The number of frames that have been transmitted by this port to its segment. Note that a frame transmitted on the interface corresponding to this port is only counted by this object if and only if it is for a protocol being processed by the local bridging function.

bridgeDot1dTpPortInDiscards.name: bridgeDot1dTpPortInDiscards
bridgeDot1dTpPortInDiscards.description: Count of valid frames received which were discarded (i.e., filtered) by the Forwarding Process.

bridgeDot1dStpProtocolSpecification.name: bridgeDot1dStpProtocolSpecification
bridgeDot1dStpProtocolSpecification.description: An indication of what version of the Spanning Tree Protocol is being run. The value 'decLb100(2)' indicates the DEC LANbridge 100 Spanning Tree protocol. IEEE 802.1d implementations will return 'ieee8021d(3)'. If future versions of the IEEE Spanning Tree Protocol are released that are incompatible with the current version a new value will be defined.

bridgeDot1dStpPriority.name: bridgeDot1dStpPriority
bridgeDot1dStpPriority.description: The value of the write-able portion of the Bridge ID, i.e., the first two octets of the (8 octet long) Bridge ID. The other (last) 6 octets of the Bridge ID are given by the value of dot1dBaseBridgeAddress.

bridgeDot1dStpTimeSinceTopologyChange.name: bridgeDot1dStpTimeSinceTopologyChange
bridgeDot1dStpTimeSinceTopologyChange.description: The time (in hundredths of a second) since the last time a topology change was detected by the bridge entity.

bridgeDot1dStpTopChanges.name: bridgeDot1dStpTopChanges
bridgeDot1dStpTopChanges.description: The total number of topology changes detected by this bridge since the management entity was last reset or initialized.

bridgeDot1dStpDesignatedRoot.name: bridgeDot1dStpDesignatedRoot
bridgeDot1dStpDesignatedRoot.description: The bridge identifier of the root of the spanning tree as determined by the Spanning Tree Protocol as executed by this node. This value is used as the Root Identifier parameter in all Configuration Bridge PDUs originated by this node.

bridgeDot1dStpRootCost.name: bridgeDot1dStpRootCost
bridgeDot1dStpRootCost.description: The cost of the path to the root as seen from this bridge.

bridgeDot1dStpRootPort.name: bridgeDot1dStpRootPort
bridgeDot1dStpRootPort.description: The port number of the port which offers the lowest cost path from this bridge to the root bridge.

bridgeDot1dStpMaxAge.name: bridgeDot1dStpMaxAge
bridgeDot1dStpMaxAge.description: The maximum age of Spanning Tree Protocol information learned from the network on any port before it is discarded, in units of hundredths of a second. This is the actual value that this bridge is currently using.

bridgeDot1dStpHelloTime.name: bridgeDot1dStpHelloTime
bridgeDot1dStpHelloTime.description: The amount of time between the transmission of Configuration bridge PDUs by this node on any port when it is the root of the spanning tree or trying to become so, in units of hundredths of a second. This is the actual value that this bridge is currently using.

bridgeDot1dStpHoldTime.name: bridgeDot1dStpHoldTime
bridgeDot1dStpHoldTime.description: This time value determines the interval length during which no more than two Configuration bridge PDUs shall be transmitted by this node, in units of hundredths of a second.

bridgeDot1dStpForwardDelay.name: bridgeDot1dStpForwardDelay
bridgeDot1dStpForwardDelay.description: This time value, measured in units of hundredths of a second, controls how fast a port changes its spanning state when moving towards the Forwarding state. The value determines how long the port stays in a particular state before moving to the next state. For example, how long a port stays in the Listening state when moving from Blocking to Learning. This value is also used, when a topology change has been detected and is underway, to age all dynamic entries in the Forwarding Database. [Note that this value is the one that this bridge is currently using, in contrast to dot1dStpBridgeForwardDelay which is the value that this bridge and all others would start using if/when this bridge were to become the root.]

bridgeDot1dStpBridgeMaxAge.name: bridgeDot1dStpBridgeMaxAge
bridgeDot1dStpBridgeMaxAge.description: The value that all bridges use for MaxAge when this bridge is acting as the root. Note that 802.1d/D9 specifies that the range for this parameter is related to the value of dot1dStpBridgeHelloTime. The granularity of this timer is specified by 802.1d/D9 to be 1 second. An agent may return a badValue error if a set is attempted to a value which is not a whole number of seconds.

bridgeDot1dStpBridgeHelloTime.name: bridgeDot1dStpBridgeHelloTime
bridgeDot1dStpBridgeHelloTime.description: The value that all bridges use for HelloTime when this bridge is acting as the root. The granularity of this timer is specified by 802.1d/D9 to be 1 second. An agent may return a badValue error if a set is attempted to a value which is not a whole number of seconds.

bridgeDot1dStpBridgeForwardDelay.name: bridgeDot1dStpBridgeForwardDelay
bridgeDot1dStpBridgeForwardDelay.description: The value that all bridges use for ForwardDelay when this bridge is acting as the root. Note that 802.1d/D9 specifies that the range for this parameter is related to the value of dot1dStpBridgeMaxAge. The granularity of this timer is specified by 802.1d/D9 to be 1 second. An agent may return a badValue error if a set is attempted to a value which is not a whole number of seconds.

bridgeStpPortTable.name: bridgeStpPortTable
bridgeStpPortTable.description: A table that contains port-specific information for the Spanning Tree Protocol.

bridgeStpPortEntry.name: bridgeStpPortEntry
bridgeStpPortEntry.description: A list of information maintained by every port about the Spanning Tree Protocol state for that port.

bridgeDot1dStpPort.name: bridgeDot1dStpPort
bridgeDot1dStpPort.description: The port number of the port for which this entry contains Spanning Tree Protocol management information.

bridgeDot1dStpPortPriority.name: bridgeDot1dStpPortPriority
bridgeDot1dStpPortPriority.description: The value of the priority field which is contained in the first (in network byte order) octet of the (2 octet long) Port ID. The other octet of the Port ID is given by the value of dot1dStpPort.

bridgeDot1dStpPortState.name: bridgeDot1dStpPortState
bridgeDot1dStpPortState.description: The port's current state as defined by application of the Spanning Tree Protocol. This state controls what action a port takes on reception of a frame. If the bridge has detected a port that is malfunctioning it will place that port into the broken(6) state. For ports which are disabled (see dot1dStpPortEnable), this object will have a value of disabled(1).

bridgeDot1dStpPortEnable.name: bridgeDot1dStpPortEnable
bridgeDot1dStpPortEnable.description: The enabled/disabled status of the port.

bridgeDot1dStpPortPathCost.name: bridgeDot1dStpPortPathCost
bridgeDot1dStpPortPathCost.description: The contribution of this port to the path cost of paths towards the spanning tree root which include this port.

bridgeDot1dStpPortDesignatedRoot.name: bridgeDot1dStpPortDesignatedRoot
bridgeDot1dStpPortDesignatedRoot.description: The unique Bridge Identifier of the Bridge recorded as the Root in the Configuration BPDUs transmitted by the Designated Bridge for the segment to which the port is attached.

bridgeDot1dStpPortDesignatedCost.name: bridgeDot1dStpPortDesignatedCost
bridgeDot1dStpPortDesignatedCost.description: The path cost of the Designated Port of the segment connected to this port. This value is compared to the Root Path Cost field in received bridge PDUs.

bridgeDot1dStpPortDesignatedBridge.name: bridgeDot1dStpPortDesignatedBridge
bridgeDot1dStpPortDesignatedBridge.description: The Bridge Identifier of the bridge which this port considers to be the Designated Bridge for this port's segment.

bridgeDot1dStpPortDesignatedPort.name: bridgeDot1dStpPortDesignatedPort
bridgeDot1dStpPortDesignatedPort.description: The Port Identifier of the port on the Designated Bridge for this port's segment.

bridgeDot1dStpPortForwardTransitions.name: bridgeDot1dStpPortForwardTransitions
bridgeDot1dStpPortForwardTransitions.description: The number of times this port has transitioned from the Learning state to the Forwarding state.

bridgeStaticTable.name: bridgeStaticTable
bridgeStaticTable.description: A table containing filtering information configured into the bridge by (local or network) management specifying the set of ports to which frames received from specific ports and containing specific destination addresses are allowed to be forwarded. The value of zero in this table as the port number from which frames with a specific destination address are received, is used to specify all ports for which there is no specific entry in this table for that particular destination address. Entries are valid for unicast and for group/broadcast addresses.

bridgeStaticEntry.name: bridgeStaticEntry
bridgeStaticEntry.description: Filtering information configured into the bridge by (local or network) management specifying the set of ports to which frames received from a specific port and containing a specific destination address are allowed to be forwarded.

bridgeDot1dStaticAddress.name: bridgeDot1dStaticAddress
bridgeDot1dStaticAddress.description: The destination MAC address in a frame to which this entry's filtering information applies. This object can take the value of a unicast address, a group address or the broadcast address.

bridgeDot1dStaticReceivePort.name: bridgeDot1dStaticReceivePort
bridgeDot1dStaticReceivePort.description: Either the value '0', or the port number of the port from which a frame must be received in order for this entry's filtering information to apply. A value of zero indicates that this entry applies on all ports of the bridge for which there is no other applicable entry.

bridgeDot1dStaticAllowedToGoTo.name: bridgeDot1dStaticAllowedToGoTo
bridgeDot1dStaticAllowedToGoTo.description: This attribute contains a representation of the Outbound Ports associated with this static entry.

bridgeDot1dStaticStatus.name: bridgeDot1dStaticStatus
bridgeDot1dStaticStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. invalid(2) - writing this value to the object removes the corresponding entry. permanent(3) - this entry is currently in use and will remain so after the next reset of the bridge. deleteOnReset(4) - this entry is currently in use and will remain so until the next reset of the bridge. deleteOnTimeout(5) - this entry is currently in use and will remain so until it is aged out.

bridgeProtFiltTable.name: bridgeProtFiltTable
bridgeProtFiltTable.description: A table containing protocol filtering information configured into the bridge by (local or network) management specifying the set of ports to which frames containing protocol ID are allowed to be forwarded.

bridgeProtFiltEntry.name: bridgeProtFiltEntry
bridgeProtFiltEntry.description: Protocol filtering information configured into the bridge by (local or network) management.

brProtFiltIndex.name: brProtFiltIndex
brProtFiltIndex.description: This attribute is used as a unique identifier into the Bridge Protocol Filtering Table.

brProtFiltName.name: brProtFiltName
brProtFiltName.description: A text string of up to 32 characters, of locally determined significance used to identify this Protocol filter.

brProtFiltId.name: brProtFiltId
brProtFiltId.description: This attribute identifies the protocol type to be filtered.

brProtFiltPortMap.name: brProtFiltPortMap
brProtFiltPortMap.description: This attribute contains a representation of the Outbound Ports associated with this static entry.

bridgeProtPriorityTable.name: bridgeProtPriorityTable
bridgeProtPriorityTable.description: A table containing protocol priority information configured into the bridge by (local or network) management specifying the priority in which frames will be transmitted on the wide area network links.

bridgeProtPriorityEntry.name: bridgeProtPriorityEntry
bridgeProtPriorityEntry.description: Protocol priority information configured into the bridge by (local or network) management.

brProtPriorityIndex.name: brProtPriorityIndex
brProtPriorityIndex.description: This attribute is used as a unique identifier into the Bridge Protocol Priority Table.

brProtPriorityName.name: brProtPriorityName
brProtPriorityName.description: A text string of up to 32 characters, of locally determined significance used to identify this Protocol Priority entry.

brProtPriorityId.name: brProtPriorityId
brProtPriorityId.description: This attribute identifies the protocol type to be prioritized.

brProtPriorityLevel.name: brProtPriorityLevel
brProtPriorityLevel.description: The priority assigned to the associated Portocol ID

wanPhysTable.name: wanPhysTable
wanPhysTable.description: This table represent a view of Management Facilities for WAN physical ports.

wanPhysEntry.name: wanPhysEntry
wanPhysEntry.description: This list contains counters and parameters related to the management of WAN ports.

wanPhysPortId.name: wanPhysPortId
wanPhysPortId.description: This attribute is used as a unique identifier for the Bridge WAN interface.

wanPhysPortName.name: wanPhysPortName
wanPhysPortName.description: A text string of up to 32 characters, of locally determined significance used to identify this WAN interface.

wanPhysLogicalPort.name: wanPhysLogicalPort
wanPhysLogicalPort.description: This attribute shows the logical port for this Wan interface. Redundant links will have the same logical port.

wanPhysDcdLevel.name: wanPhysDcdLevel
wanPhysDcdLevel.description: This attribute shows the level of the DCD EIA signal on this particular WAN link.

wanPhysLinkLevel.name: wanPhysLinkLevel
wanPhysLinkLevel.description: This attribute shows whether the WAN link is 'up' or 'down'.

wanTxLinkUtilization.name: wanTxLinkUtilization
wanTxLinkUtilization.description: This attribute shows the link utilization in the TX direction. The utilization is a percentage of the bandwidth (0 to 100).

wanRxLinkUtilization.name: wanRxLinkUtilization
wanRxLinkUtilization.description: This attribute shows the link utilization in the RX direction. The utilization is a percentage of the bandwidth (0 to 100).

wanPhysFrameErrors.name: wanPhysFrameErrors
wanPhysFrameErrors.description: This attribute shows the number of frame errors on this WAN interface.

wanCompressionState.name: wanCompressionState
wanCompressionState.description: This attribute shows whether data compression is enabled or disabled.

wanCompressionRatio.name: wanCompressionRatio
wanCompressionRatio.description: An indication of how well the Bridge is compressing data that is to be transmitted to another bridge. A value of 100 shows no compression, a value of 300 shows a 3 : 1 compression.

ieeeIfTable.name: ieeeIfTable
ieeeIfTable.description: This table represent a view of Management Facilities for the IEEE802.3 CSMA/CD MAC layer. The object was defined by IEEE in a 802.3 standard.

ieeeIfEntry.name: ieeeIfEntry
ieeeIfEntry.description: This list contains counters and parameters related to the management of the IEEE802.3 MAC layer.

ieeeIfIndex.name: ieeeIfIndex
ieeeIfIndex.description: This attribute is used as a unique identifier for the Bridge LAN interface.

ieeeFrmsTxOk.name: ieeeFrmsTxOk
ieeeFrmsTxOk.description: This attribute contains a count of frames that are successfully transmitted.

ieeeSingleCollFrms.name: ieeeSingleCollFrms
ieeeSingleCollFrms.description: This attribute contains a count of frames that are involved in a single collision and are subsequently transmitted successfuly.

ieeeMultipleCollFrms.name: ieeeMultipleCollFrms
ieeeMultipleCollFrms.description: This attribute contains a count of frames that are involved in more than one collision and are subsequently transmitted successfully.

ieeeOctetsTxOk.name: ieeeOctetsTxOk
ieeeOctetsTxOk.description: This attribute contains a count of data and padding octets in frames that are successfully transmitted.

ieeeDefTx.name: ieeeDefTx
ieeeDefTx.description: This attribute contains a count of frames whose transmission was delayed on its first attempt becasue the medium was busy.

ieeeMcastFrmsTxOk.name: ieeeMcastFrmsTxOk
ieeeMcastFrmsTxOk.description: This attribute contains a count of frames that are successfully transmitted as indicated by the status value transmitOK, to a group destination address other than broadcast.

ieeeBcastFrmsTxOk.name: ieeeBcastFrmsTxOk
ieeeBcastFrmsTxOk.description: This attribute contains a number of broadcast frames transmitted to the LAN connection.

ieeeLateColls.name: ieeeLateColls
ieeeLateColls.description: This attribute contains a count of the times that a collision has been detected later than 512 bit times into the transmitted packet.

ieeeExcessColls.name: ieeeExcessColls
ieeeExcessColls.description: This attribute contains a count of frames that due to excessive collisions are not transmitted successfully.

ieeeIntlMacTxError.name: ieeeIntlMacTxError
ieeeIntlMacTxError.description: This attribute contains a count of frames which would otherwise be transmitted by the station,but could not be sent due to an internal MAC sublayer transmit error.

ieeeCsErrors.name: ieeeCsErrors
ieeeCsErrors.description: This attribute contains number of frames that were lost because the ethernet carrier signal was lost.

ieeeExcessDef.name: ieeeExcessDef
ieeeExcessDef.description: This attribute contains a count of frames which deferred for an excessive period of time.

ieeeFrmsRxOk.name: ieeeFrmsRxOk
ieeeFrmsRxOk.description: This attribute contains a count of frames that are successfully received.

ieeeOctetsRxOk.name: ieeeOctetsRxOk
ieeeOctetsRxOk.description: This attribute contains a count of data and padding octets in frames that are successfully received.

ieeeMcastFrmsRxOk.name: ieeeMcastFrmsRxOk
ieeeMcastFrmsRxOk.description: This attribute contains a count of frames that are successfully received and are directed to an active non-broadcast group of addresses.

ieeeBcastFrmsRxOk.name: ieeeBcastFrmsRxOk
ieeeBcastFrmsRxOk.description: This attribute contains a number of broadcast frames received from the LAN connection.

ieeeTooLongErrors.name: ieeeTooLongErrors
ieeeTooLongErrors.description: This attribute contains a count of frames that are received and exceeded the maximum permitted frame size. This counter is incremented when the status of a frame reception is frame TooLong.

ieeeAlignErrors.name: ieeeAlignErrors
ieeeAlignErrors.description: This attribute contains a count of frames that are not an integral of octets in length and do not pass the Frame Check Sequence(FCS) check.This counter is incremented when the ReceiveStatus is reported as alignmentError.

ieeeFcsErrors.name: ieeeFcsErrors
ieeeFcsErrors.description: This attribute contains a count of frames that are an integral of octets in length and do not pass the Frame Check Sequence(FCS) check. This counter is incremented when the ReceiveStatus is reported as frameCheckError.

ieeeIrLengthErrors.name: ieeeIrLengthErrors
ieeeIrLengthErrors.description: This attribute contains a count of frames with a length field value, between the minimum unpadded LLC data size and the maximum allowed LLC data size inclusive, that does not match the number of LLC data octets received. The counter also contains frames with a length field value less than the minimum unpadded LLC data size.

ieeeOorLengthFields.name: ieeeOorLengthFields
ieeeOorLengthFields.description: This attribute contains a count of frames with a length field value greater than the maximum allowed LLC data size.

ieeeIntlMacRcvErrors.name: ieeeIntlMacRcvErrors
ieeeIntlMacRcvErrors.description: This attribute contains a count of frames which would otherwise be received by the station,but could not be accepted due to an internal MAC sublayer receive error.

ieeeInitMac.name: ieeeInitMac
ieeeInitMac.description: This attributes indicates wether the underlying IEEE 802.3 MAC was initialized.

ieeePromRxStatus.name: ieeePromRxStatus
ieeePromRxStatus.description: This attribute contains the current state of the Prom.

ieeeMacSubLayerStatus.name: ieeeMacSubLayerStatus
ieeeMacSubLayerStatus.description: This attribute contains the current state of the Receive side of the underlying IEEE 802.3 resource.

ieeeTxStatus.name: ieeeTxStatus
ieeeTxStatus.description: This attribute contains the current state of the Transmit side of the underlying IEEE 802.3 resource.

ieeeMcastRxStatus.name: ieeeMcastRxStatus
ieeeMcastRxStatus.description: This attribute specifies if Multicast frames will be received by the underlying IEEE 802.3 resource.

ieeeMacAddress.name: ieeeMacAddress
ieeeMacAddress.description: This attribute contains the specific MAC Address of the individual MAC Entity associated with the Port.

ieeeSqeTestErrors.name: ieeeSqeTestErrors
ieeeSqeTestErrors.description: This attribute contains a count of errors detected when performing an SQE test. This counter is not currently supported.

ganEventLogEntry.name: ganEventLogEntry
ganEventLogEntry.description: Log information of alarms generated by the product, including time of event, severity and description.

ganEventLogIndex.name: ganEventLogIndex
ganEventLogIndex.description: An index to the alarm table, not relevant other than to display the table.

ganEventLogDate.name: ganEventLogDate
ganEventLogDate.description: This date on which the event causing the alarm to be generated occurred.

ganEventLogTime.name: ganEventLogTime
ganEventLogTime.description: This time at which the event causing the alarm to be generated occurred.

ganEventLogEventNum.name: ganEventLogEventNum
ganEventLogEventNum.description: An index to the alarm table, not relevant other than to display the table. This attribute has been deprecated because it duplicates the ganEventLogIndex.

ganEventLogSeverity.name: ganEventLogSeverity
ganEventLogSeverity.description: An index to the event log table, not relevant other than to display the table.

ganEventLogDescription.name: ganEventLogDescription
ganEventLogDescription.description: Textual description of the event log.

snmpCommunityTable.name: snmpCommunityTable
snmpCommunityTable.description: This table provide a management view of which device can poll this resource via SNMP based on the Community Name, IP address and Privilege. Sets are supported ONLY in the Gandalf WAN proxy agent. To set a new community entry, use the instance 25 as the index value. Example: snmpCommunityName.25 Set all objects in the entry using instance 25. When the last object is set, the agent checks for duplicate entries and returns an error status if any found, otherwise the new entry is inserted at the next available position in the table. Existing entries may be modified by setting the a new value using an existing instance. The agent rejects any attempt to duplicate an entry. Objects may be deleted by setting the community name to one or more spaces. The entry is deleted and any vacated row is filled in by moving the last valid row there. NOTE: The object snmpTrapRemotePort is not supported in the Gandalf WAN Proxy agent.

snmpCommunityEntry.name: snmpCommunityEntry
snmpCommunityEntry.description: This is a list of attributes that make the Community Table.

snmpCommunityIndex.name: snmpCommunityIndex
snmpCommunityIndex.description: An 8 bit value unique within the Community Name.

snmpCommunityName.name: snmpCommunityName
snmpCommunityName.description: The name of a Community supported by this SNMP agent.

snmpCommunityIpAddr.name: snmpCommunityIpAddr
snmpCommunityIpAddr.description: The Ip Address of a manager associated with a Community that will be supported by the SNMP agent. A value of zero means that all managers from that Community will be supported.

snmpCommunityPriv.name: snmpCommunityPriv
snmpCommunityPriv.description: The access priviledge associated with a Community.

snmpTrapCommunityTable.name: snmpTrapCommunityTable
snmpTrapCommunityTable.description: This table provide a management view of which device(s) (i.e. LAN Managers) this resource will send Trap to. Sets are supported ONLY in the Gandalf WAN proxy agent. To set a new community entry, use the instance 25 as the index value. Example: snmpTrapCommunityName.25 Set all objects in the entry using instance 25. When the last object is set, the agent checks for duplicate entries and returns an error status if any found, otherwise the new entry is inserted at the next available position in the table. Existing entries may be modified by setting the a new value using an existing instance. The agent rejects any attempt to duplicate an entry. Objects may be deleted by setting the community name to one or more spaces. The entry is deleted and any vacated row is filled in by moving the last valid row there.

snmpTrapCommunityEntry.name: snmpTrapCommunityEntry
snmpTrapCommunityEntry.description: This is a list of attributes that make the Trap Community Table.

snmpTrapCommunityIndex.name: snmpTrapCommunityIndex
snmpTrapCommunityIndex.description: An 8 bit value unique within the Community Name.

snmpTrapCommunityName.name: snmpTrapCommunityName
snmpTrapCommunityName.description: The name of a Trap Community associated with a LAN Manager.

snmpTrapIpAddr.name: snmpTrapIpAddr
snmpTrapIpAddr.description: The Ip Address of a manager that will receive Traps generated by this SNMP agent.

snmpTrapRemotePort.name: snmpTrapRemotePort
snmpTrapRemotePort.description: The remote UDP port number used by an agent to receive Traps (usually port 162 is used).

snmpTrapDescription.name: snmpTrapDescription
snmpTrapDescription.description: This attribute provide a description of Enterprise Specific Traps. This is also known as the 'interesting information' of an Enterprise Specific Trap.

gCardInstalled.name: gCardInstalled
gCardInstalled.description: This trap indicates that a card was physically installed in the hub. The trap description identify the card slot number.

gCardRemoved.name: gCardRemoved
gCardRemoved.description: This trap indicates that a card was physically removed from the hub. The trap description identify the card slot number.

gCardMismatch.name: gCardMismatch
gCardMismatch.description: This trap indicates that a card was physically installed in a slot configured with a different card type.

gCardMismatchCleared.name: gCardMismatchCleared
gCardMismatchCleared.description: This trap indicates that the slot causing a Card Mismatch was reconfigured with the proper card type.

gPortThresholdExceeded.name: gPortThresholdExceeded
gPortThresholdExceeded.description: This trap indicates a time based or frame based threshold is exceeded on a given port. The trap description will indicate the type of threshold, as well as identifing the card and port number.

gNvramFault.name: gNvramFault
gNvramFault.description: This trap indicates a critical hardware failure: an NVRAM fault.

gFiltDatabaseFull.name: gFiltDatabaseFull
gFiltDatabaseFull.description: This trap indicates that the number of entries in the Filtering Database has reached the bridge's storing capacity.

gPowerSupplyFailed.name: gPowerSupplyFailed
gPowerSupplyFailed.description: This trap indicates that a fault was detected on a power supply. The trap description will indicate which of the two power supply is faulty.

gLogThresholdExceeded.name: gLogThresholdExceeded
gLogThresholdExceeded.description: This trap indicates that the event log capacity was exceeded.

gLinkMismatch.name: gLinkMismatch
gLinkMismatch.description: This trap indicates that the configuration of a WAN port is incompatible with the network topology.

gLinkMismatchCleared.name: gLinkMismatchCleared
gLinkMismatchCleared.description: This trap indicates that the condition causing a Link Mismatch was corrected.

gNewRoot.name: gNewRoot
gNewRoot.description: The newRoot trap indicates that the sending agent has become the new root of the Spanning Tree; the trap is sent by a bridge soon after its election as the new root, e.g., upon expiration of the Topology Change Timer immediately subsequent to its election.

gTopologyChange.name: gTopologyChange
gTopologyChange.description: A topologyChange trap is sent by a bridge when any of its configured ports transitions from the Learning state to the Forwarding state, or from the Forwarding state to the Blocking state. The trap is not sent if a newRoot trap is sent for the same transition.

gPortFailure.name: gPortFailure
gPortFailure.description: A link to a port has failed. Possible reasons: 1. Master port idle receive timer has expired. Port has been disabled and declared faulty. Standby port will take over if ready. 2. Standby port idle receive timer has expired. Port has been disabled and declared faulty.
